// HoldMode is the per-leg hold state. Two non-OFF modes because the
// holder and the holdee need different behaviour during a bridged
// hold:
//
//	alice holds bob:
//	  alice's leg → MUTE (her outgoing relay is dropped so bob
//	               doesn't hear her; her UA already mutes locally,
//	               so no MOH from us either)
//	  bob's leg   → MOH  (his outgoing relay is dropped so alice
//	               doesn't hear him; we pump MOH to him so he
//	               doesn't think the call dropped)
